Saham Unitrust Insurance Nigeria Limited’s group’s Gross Written Premium (GWP) rose by 27 per cent to N3.168 billion at the end of December, 2018, from N2.486 billion at the end of December, 2017. This was disclosed in the company’s 2018 financial report which was approved by the regulatory authority of the insurance industry, the National Insurance Commission (NAICOM). The increase in the group’s level of activity was mainly attributable to strategic partnership and increase in market drive. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Saham Unitrust posts N2.486bn premium growth in 2017 Saham Unitrust Insurance posts N429.9m profit Saham Unitrust Insurance paid N350m claims in Q2